  "text": "Multiple analysis of variance showed a significant effect of genotype on plasma cortisol concentration, plasma ALT, AST, CK and LDH enzyme activities and pH 0 and pH 2 from LT muscle. Table V shows least square means from these parameters but the relationship between lairage time and stress susceptibility could not be demonstrated because there were not enough animals in each group. Sex (Tab. VI) showed a significant effect on Hb, plasma enzyme activities, pH [CITATION_1] LT and FOP 24 SM, with blood parameters higher in females and muscle parameters higher in males.",
